the agriculture department says plans are 
being made for agricultural trade and development missions to 
pakistan and bangladesh 
undersecretary richard crowder said a mission also will be sent 
to india which had been visited earlier under trade mission 
program no dates have been set he said 
these three south asian countries imported 1 billion worth of 
us agricultural products last year crowder said in his recent 
announcement 
in addition pakistan and bangladesh are two of our largest 
food aid recipients these missions offer an excellent opportunity 
to review all us trade and development programs and make 
recommendations for improved coordination with the three 
countries 
the missions will include representatives from the departments 
of agriculture and state and the us agency for international 
development three to six private representatives also will be 
selected for each team 
congress authorized the missions program two years ago to 
encourage greater us private sector and foreign country 
participation in us agricultural trade and development 
activities sixteen countries have been visited or are planned 
under the program 
