for germans this is a time of 
happiness relief and even national pride after four decades of 
living with the cold war division of the two countries 
the opening of east germanys borders and the crumbling of the 
berlin wall at times seemed impossible but then happened overnight 
this is our germany our country said an exuberant lutz 
hermann of east berlin as he joined hundreds of thousands of others 
in passing freely through the wall to the west 
germans long have been engulfed by the cold war a product of 
adolf hitlers murderous nazi legacy 
the wall in berlin the communist border fortifications the 
east germans gunned down trying to escape to the west formed a part 
of daily life 
now with the wall a relic of the past and borders between the 
countries open germans who embraced each with tears of joy sense 
that an end to the cold war division may be within reach 
in recent days as the world looks upon berlin and germany no 
one needs to be ashamed of his tears said the conservative 
frankfurter allgemeine zeitung newspaper in a frontpage editorial 
sunday 
the newspaper in a special edition marking east germanys new 
border policy added they the germans have had to live long 
enough with a border that has ripped apart villages and families 
even west germanys leftist politicians long skeptical of 
demands for german reunification in recent days have become fond 
of quoting the national anthems call for unity as well as 
justice and freedom for the german nation 
in east berlin the euphoric reaction has come from the people 
rather than from the government which remains fiercely opposed to 
any trends toward reunification 
millions of ordinary east germans poured into the west over the 
weekend in the largest eastwest party in history 
yet the happiness relief and pride still leave many issues 
open 
in east germany the government still must figure out which way 
to turn now that it has raised the peoples hopes to a fever pitch 
giving people the freedom to travel wont solve the massive 
problems caused by the exodus of tens of thousands nor will it 
solve such tricky questions as whether east berlin will allow truly 
free elections 
in west germany national pride itself remains a sensitive 
issue as rightwing extremists preach a message of being proud 
to be german and make startling political gains 
bonn also also faces enormous difficulties now that west 
germany has taken on the burden of absorbing so many east german 
refugees 
the question is whether bonn after years of urging open 
borders will erect its own restrictions to keep out east germans 
by means of a kind of invisible wall 
both countries remain at the front lines of officially hostile 
military alliances with 250000 us soldiers stationed in west 
germany and nearly 400000 soviet troops in east germany 
the nazi legacy itself will still be an issue for germans 
despite the growing complaint from conservative historians that it 
is a past that will not go into the past 
newspaper editorials leading intellectuals and politicians on 
sunday all expressed ambivalent feelings welcoming the east 
germans new freedom but questioning the dangers posed by a united 
germany 
