j lee iii the white house physician and william french smith 
attorney general in the reagan administration 
with drug policy director william bennett at his side bush 
urged the advisors to find better ways to 
encourage employers to keep workplaces drugfree 
enlist the aid of volunteers in the fight against drugs 
communicate to all americans especially our young the 
importance of staying off drugs 
coordinate existing private and nonprofit antidrug efforts 
involve the private sector in the building of prisons and 
jails 
bush unveiled a nearly 8 billion antidrug strategy two months 
ago 
