<TEXT>
a farm couple who hired drifters to buy 
cattle was charged monday with killing three former employees whose 
bodies were found in northern missouri barns last month 
attorney general william webster announced the filing of 
firstdegree murder charges against ray copeland 75 of 
mooresville and his wife faye 68 at a news conference at the 
livingston county jail 
the copelands have been held in the jail since oct 9 on charges 
of conspiracy to steal cattle with bad checks from an account set 
up for an employee the conspiracy charge was dismissed monday but 
