dropped a 200 million credit stabilization plan for poland a plan 
he said republicans believed would be unworkable 
sen paul simon dill chief sponsor of the democratic aid 
plan said the compromise makes senate approval of the package on 
tuesday virtually certain 
the elevation of members of the solidarity trade union to 
leadership positions in the polish government precipitated events 
in east germany simon said 
