the philadelphia stock exchange plans to 
extend its trading day in foreign currency options by 6 hours to 
coincide with trading in far east and pacific countries 
under the plan the exchange will remain open for foreign 
currency options from 10 pm its current close of evening 
trading until 430 am when it now begins its morning session 
the exchange will continue to be closed from 230 pm to 6 pm 
the new hours which will allow trading for a total of 20 hours 
a day will begin in early 1990 spokeswoman nancy tague said 
friday 
the philadelphia stock exchange continues to respond to the 
needs of market participants around the world said nicholas 
giordano president of the exchange the success of our 
eveningearly morning trading sessions reinforces our decision to 
extend the trading hours 
in 1987 the philadelphia exchange became the nations first to 
introduce a night trading session in january it became the first 
to start an earlymorning trading session 
the exchange trades in five major currencies in the evening 
session and eight major currencies in the day session 
