the investment group condor partners took a step 
monday toward wresting control of ual corp from its board of 
directors which in turn authorized its financial adviser to 
explore alternatives to a takeover of the parent of united airlines 
condor formed as a takeover vehicle by the new york investment 
group coniston partners gained access to a list of ual 
stockholders monday by submitting certain documents to the company 
this enables the group to send consent solicitation materials to 
the stockholders seeking their approval for removing certain board 
members 
the documents did not disclose the terms or financing of any 
proposals that coniston might contemplate the board said in a 
statement after it met monday 
the board said it has authorized its financial adviser first 
boston corp to explore potential transactions with third 
parties including actively determining available alternative 
transactions such as employee ownership or recapitalization 
the board said it has not received any offers from third parties 
coniston announced nov 3 that it owned 97 percent of ual and 
wanted to direct a sale recapitalization or other extraordinary 
transaction involving the chicagobased company 
coniston also wants to reduce uals board from 16 members to 
five three of whom would be coniston principals 
the board said monday that the two directors coniston wants to 
retain stephen wolf and frank olson have indicated they would not 
serve on any ual board controlled by coniston wolf is uals 
chairman president and chief executive officer 
mondays board meeting was the first since directors freed wolf 
to explore new options following a collapsed employee effort to buy 
the company 
uals shares closed monday at 19325 up 375 in consolidated 
new york stock exchange trading 
