new york said that given the failure of the 675 billion buyout 
bid by uniteds pilots a management team and british airways plc 
there are significant numbers of ual shareholders who are 
sympathetic toward coniston 
speculators want to see ual sold or recapitalized quickly to 
minimize their losses following the oct 13 collapse of the 
300ashare bid from the pilotmanagement group 
if i were on the board i would assume that there are 
sufficient shares held by accounts sympathetic to coniston that 
would result in a majority vote against the board buttrick said 
analysts said ual began its defense against conistons attempt 
to seize control of its board when it gave wolf permission to seek 
a buyout or recapitalization 
